Haast, is a dynamic AI-led regtech start-up shaking up the marketing compliance world. Using the latest in AI and ML, we analyse multimodal data sources (web, social media, images, video) to enable issue detection and remediation in seconds. Haast is already integral in keeping a range of organisations compliant, reducing risk and unlocking a vast amount of productivity gains. 



We are seeking an experienced Fullstack Engineer to join our innovative team. We are looking for a tech enthusiast who thrives in a fast-paced environment and is passionate about developing scalable and efficient software solutions.

Develop and maintain the Haast web platform (built in Flask and Svelte)
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features.
Manage and mentor junior developers
Report development progress to founders
Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications.
Identify and fix bugs; continuously improve performance including identifying and correcting bottlenecks
Help maintain code quality, organisation, and automatisation.
Maintain and upgrade CI/CD pipeline




Essential Skills & Experience:

3+ years of experience in fullstack development.
Proficiency in Python, and JavaScript.
Strong experience in large data collection, AI, and data visualisation.
Familiar with various design and architectural patterns.
Experience with database technologies (PostgresSQL).
Experience with search technologies
Ability to develop with UX in at the front of mind
Knowledge of code versioning tools (such as Git).


Desirable:
Proficiency in Flask and Svelte
Experience in a start-up environment.
Familiarity with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP).
Interest in machine learning
Experience with Apache Airflow
Experience with GitHub Actions


Benefits:

Competitive salary package plus Employee Stock Option Plan (ESOP).
Flexible working hours and work-from-home options.
Continuous learning and development opportunities.
Dynamic and supportive work environment.

Please send your resume and a cover letter outlining your experience and why you would be a great fit for this role to liam@haast.io


Applications should discuss projects and link to code repositories where possible.


We thank all applicants for their interest, however, only those candidates selected for interviews will be contacted.


Sydney preferred, all of Australia considered

**Job Summary:**
We're seeking an experienced Senior Software Engineer to join our team in Sydney (with flexible remote work options) or San Francisco (with occasional travel to Sydney). As a Senior Software Engineer, you will play a critical role in designing, developing, and delivering world-class AI-powered software solutions that meet the highest standards of quality and performance. You will collaborate with our cross-functional team of engineers, researchers, and product managers to deliver innovative solutions that drive business growth and customer satisfaction.

**Responsibilities:**

* Design, develop, test, and deploy scalable, secure, and efficient software systems that integrate with our AI platform
* Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify and prioritize project requirements, develop project plans, and deliver high-quality software solutions on time and within budget
* Lead the development of new features and maintain existing ones, ensuring that they meet the highest standards of quality, security, and performance
* Participate in code reviews, provide constructive feedback, and contribute to the improvement of the overall code quality
* Stay up-to-date with the latest trends and advancements in AI, machine learning, and software engineering, and apply this knowledge to improve our products and services
* Mentor junior engineers, share knowledge, and contribute to the growth of the team
* Collaborate with DevOps engineers to ensure the smooth deployment and operation of our software systems

**Requirements:**

* 5+ years of experience in software development, with a focus on AI, machine learning, or related fields
* Strong proficiency in one or more programming languages, such as Python, Java, or C++
* Experience with cloud-based technologies, such as AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud
* Strong understanding of software design patterns, data structures, and algorithms
* Familiarity with Agile development methodologies and version control systems, such as Git
* Excellent problem-solving skills, with the ability to debug and optimize complex software systems
* Strong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in a distributed team
* Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field

**Nice to Have:**

* Experience with AI/ML frameworks, such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, or scikit-learn
* Knowledge of containerization using Docker, Kubernetes, or similar technologies
* Experience with CI/CD pipelines and automation tools, such as Jenkins or GitLab CI/CD
* Familiarity with front-end development, including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
